42:38.639 --> 42:41.517
♪ ♪

43:01.996 --> 43:03.872
♪ ♪

43:33.944 --> 43:35.946
♪ ♪

43:59.928 --> 44:01.930
♪ ♪

44:24.411 --> 44:26.372
♪ ♪

44:46.517 --> 44:49.853
♪ ♪

45:09.039 --> 45:11.041
♪ ♪

45:42.156 --> 45:43.407
(clicks)

46:02.593 --> 46:05.387
♪ ♪

46:23.780 --> 46:25.991
♪ ♪

46:45.761 --> 46:47.888
♪ ♪

47:07.908 --> 47:09.910
♪ ♪

47:30.347 --> 47:32.516
♪ ♪

48:02.671 --> 48:04.673
♪ ♪

48:24.651 --> 48:26.653
♪ ♪

48:40.208 --> 48:41.376
Hi there.

48:41.460 --> 48:43.170
You must be Beth Ann?

48:43.253 --> 48:44.838
You must be Simone.
Come in.

48:44.921 --> 48:48.008
- It's nice to finally meet you.
- Likewise.

48:48.091 --> 48:50.177
I have the keys
around here somewhere.

48:50.260 --> 48:52.012
Let me look.

48:52.095 --> 48:53.847
One of the reasons
I wanted to meet

48:53.930 --> 48:56.016
was because I had a question.

48:56.099 --> 48:57.392
It's a bit awkward.

48:57.476 --> 48:59.019
What would you like to know?

48:59.102 --> 49:00.437
The realtor told me

49:00.520 --> 49:02.856
that someone was murdered
in this house?

49:02.939 --> 49:04.858
It's true.
My husband was killed...

49:04.942 --> 49:06.026
right where you're standing.

49:06.109 --> 49:08.028
- Oh, dear.
- Our neighbor broke in

49:08.111 --> 49:09.738
and accused Rob of
sleeping with his wife.

49:09.821 --> 49:11.323
Shot him dead.

49:11.406 --> 49:13.492
He was executed last year.
So sad.

49:15.160 --> 49:17.245
Aunt Beth, I'm packed.
Can we go?

49:17.329 --> 49:19.331
In a sec.
Elsie, this is Simone,

49:19.414 --> 49:21.333
- the woman who bought our house.
- Hi, there.

49:21.416 --> 49:23.710
You're so pretty.
She's your niece?

49:23.794 --> 49:26.171
The daughter of my friend,
April Warner.

49:26.254 --> 49:28.674
But I've been helping take care
of her since she was a baby.

49:28.757 --> 49:30.509
April is a singer, you know.

49:30.592 --> 49:32.052
My mom's gonna be on Broadway.

49:32.135 --> 49:34.179
That's why we sold the house.
We're moving to New York.

49:34.262 --> 49:35.430
Oh, how exciting.

49:35.514 --> 49:36.890
Here are your keys.

49:36.973 --> 49:40.936
I hope to have a very
happy life in this house.

49:41.019 --> 49:43.063
A happy life
isn't hard to come by.

49:43.146 --> 49:46.650
The trick is
to not regret the choices

49:46.733 --> 49:49.403
you made along the way.

49:49.486 --> 49:51.363
Yes.

49:51.446 --> 49:53.365
Well...

49:53.448 --> 49:55.242
good luck with everything.

49:55.325 --> 49:57.786
Likewise.
Take care of my house.

49:58.995 --> 50:00.956
I'll give it lots of love.

50:02.833 --> 50:04.251
There you go.

50:04.334 --> 50:07.087
Thank you.

50:07.170 --> 50:08.922
I just know that we're
gonna love living here.

50:09.005 --> 50:10.590
I certainly hope so.

50:10.674 --> 50:12.467
So when did you
buy the house?

50:12.551 --> 50:14.136
'74.

50:14.219 --> 50:17.013
But after my husband died,
I rented the house out.

50:17.097 --> 50:20.767
Then it was the headquarters
for my foundation.

50:20.851 --> 50:23.061
I raise money for AIDS research.

50:23.145 --> 50:24.438
Yeah, we've read up on you.

50:24.521 --> 50:25.981
You've done such
amazing work.

50:26.064 --> 50:28.608
I ended up living
a very rich life,

50:28.692 --> 50:30.777
once I stopped worrying
about money.

50:32.362 --> 50:34.322
Paulo, I'm ready.

50:35.824 --> 50:37.284
Is that a Thomas J. Harte?

50:37.367 --> 50:40.287
- Oh, you know his work?
- TAYLOR: Sure.

50:40.370 --> 50:42.581
- Yeah, we saw a show of his at the Whitney last year.
- That's right, yeah.

50:42.664 --> 50:45.751
Oh, isn't that wonderful?

50:45.834 --> 50:47.836
I always hoped Tommy
would go far.

50:47.919 --> 50:51.590
Tommy?
Is he a friend of yours?

50:51.673 --> 50:55.635
A friend?
You could say that.

50:55.719 --> 50:58.889
My face is tattooed on his ass.

51:00.891 --> 51:03.477
Paulo, push.

51:08.023 --> 51:10.984
(sighs) Well, it's been
lovely to meet you, Taylor.

51:11.067 --> 51:12.694
And just know that
Andrew and I will

51:12.778 --> 51:14.780
take wonderful care
of your home.

51:14.863 --> 51:17.115
Aw, well, I hope
you'll enjoy it.

51:17.199 --> 51:19.159
We will.

51:19.242 --> 51:23.038
And I'm sorry for everything
that happened to you here.

51:23.121 --> 51:25.791
Can't imagine what
you went through.

51:25.874 --> 51:27.959
It was an awful night.

51:28.043 --> 51:29.461
But it could have been worse.

51:29.544 --> 51:31.838
So you really have
a rifle collection?

51:31.922 --> 51:34.174
Yeah. They're all
in that box over there.

51:34.257 --> 51:36.718
Hey, check this out.

51:36.802 --> 51:39.721
This is me on safari
in Africa.

51:39.805 --> 51:42.015
- Look at that.
- No way.

51:42.098 --> 51:44.518
Well, I-I never knew there were
Jews that were into hunting.

51:44.601 --> 51:46.853
We exist. But it's not
as cruel to the animals,

51:46.937 --> 51:48.563
because we miss so frequently.

51:50.148 --> 51:52.984
TAYLOR:
Oh, before I forget,

51:53.068 --> 51:54.486
here are your keys.

51:54.569 --> 51:57.239
Thank you.

51:57.322 --> 51:58.657
So, what about
the two of you?

51:58.740 --> 52:00.033
Found a new place to live?

52:00.116 --> 52:01.660
- Uh, yeah. Well, actually...
- (phone buzzing)

52:01.743 --> 52:04.037
...we're moving back
to our old condo.

52:04.120 --> 52:06.915
After living in a mansion.
That is some serious downsizing.

52:06.998 --> 52:09.709
Yeah. For us, it turns out...

52:09.793 --> 52:11.837
Less is more.

52:11.920 --> 52:13.213
Well, best of luck
to both of you.

52:13.296 --> 52:15.090
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

52:18.677 --> 52:20.220
They seem like nice people.

52:27.811 --> 52:29.563
Are you gonna miss the house?

52:29.646 --> 52:32.357
It's just a building.

52:32.440 --> 52:34.526
Home is where my family is.

52:53.712 --> 52:56.423
Back to the hotel?

52:56.506 --> 53:00.510
Yes. I'm ready
for my massage now.

53:02.470 --> 53:05.348
(chuckles)

53:15.358 --> 53:17.777
All right.
Condo, here we come.

53:17.861 --> 53:21.615
It's gonna be nice.
Just the three of us.

53:21.698 --> 53:24.159
(barks)

53:32.709 --> 53:33.877
Honey?

53:36.671 --> 53:38.673
(gunshot)

